Class MockDiceCup

  • java.lang.Object
    • test.MockDiceCup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDiceCup
    public class MockDiceCup
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDiceCup
    This class is a "fake" dice cup, that can be used when testing the game. This dice cup differs from the regular in that it can set predetermined values through the constructor. When all predetermined values have been used, the dice cup will then begin to act like a regular dice cup.
